steps.content:
## ðŸ”¹ Methods
A function stored inside an object is called a **method**.

```javascript
const dog = {
    name: 'Rex',
    bark: function() {
        console.log('Woof!');
    }
};

dog.bark(); // Prints: Woof!
```

## ðŸ”¹ The 'this' Keyword
To access other properties inside the same object, use `this`.
```javascript
const person = {
    name: 'Alice',
    greet: function() {
        console.log('Hello, I am ' + this.name);
    }
};

person.greet(); // Hello, I am Alice
```

